# Web automation (Playwright)

- **Persistent browser profiles** where appropriate (cookies/sessions).
- **Isolated browser contexts per task** to avoid cross-task leakage.
- Prefer **robust selectors**; avoid brittle text-only or nth-child hacks when stable roles/testids exist.
- **Retry** network/navigation/transient UI actions with backoff and sane limits.

## Always consider

Login flows, SPAs (dynamic DOM), timeouts, navigation failures.

## If stuck

Detect **no-progress loops**, capture **screenshot**, escalate to the user with context—do not spin forever.
